        "\n",
        "# Module 4: Mediation and Predictive Power\n",
        "\n",
        "This final module explains *how* these factors result in continued green product purchasing.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Section 1: Mediation Effect\n",
        "\n",
        "### Objective\n",
        "To test if \"Customer Satisfaction\" acts as a bridge mediating the effect between Brand Image and Customer Loyalty.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Statistical Perspective\n",
        "**Mediation Analysis:** Explores structurally *how* or exactly *why* a particular observed causal effect occurs. A mediating theoretical variable (Customer Satisfaction) sits exactly between an exogenous independent variable (Brand Image) and an endogenous dependent variable (Customer Loyalty).\n",
        "\n",
        "**Categorical Types of Mediation:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Full (Complete) Mediation:** The IV only affects the DV passing *through* the psychological mediator. The direct causal path becomes statistically insignificant ($p > 0.05$) when the mediator is mathematically introduced to the regression block.\n",
        "- **Partial Mediation:** The IV independently influences the DV both directly and indirectly through the mediator, indicating multiple causal mechanisms are operating simultaneously.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Criteria for Significance:** Evaluating the isolated indirect path ($a \\times b$) isn't normally distributed. Therefore, we use tools like programmatic *bootstrapping* to randomly generate 5,000 sub-samples to build 95% Confidence Intervals for the indirect effect. If precisely the confidence interval does not cross zero $[0.15, 0.40]$, the mediation is empirically significant.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Industry Application:** In digital marketing, ad-spend (IV) increases e-commerce sales (DV), but this is \"mediated\" by website traffic (Mediator). If traffic doesn't increase, sales don't increase, meaning it's a fully mediated relationship essential for tracking campaign ROI.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Python Example Code"
      ],
