        "5. In the Gogoro scenario, what serves as the mediator?\n",
        "\n",
        "## Section 2: Effect Size ($f^2$)\n",
        "\n",
        "### Objective\n",
        "To calculate the effect size to determine if the impact of variables are practically meaningful.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Statistical Perspective\n",
        "While traditional significance tests (like standard p-values) tell us categorically if an effect mathematically *exists* independent of zero, they don't objectively tell us how *meaningful*, large, or profitable that effect is in the real world. \n",
        "\n",
        "**Cohen's Effect Size ($f^2$):** \n",
        "Determines specifically the practical magnitude of heavily predicting one specific endogenous construct, isolating the isolated utility of a single predictive path.\n",
        "Calculated as the difference in global explanation power: $f^2 = \\frac{R^2_{included} - R^2_{excluded}}{1 - R^2_{included}}$\n",
        "\n",
        "**Rigid Practical Criteria:**\n",
        "\n",
        "According to Cohen (1988), effect sizes quantitatively distinguish causal relevance:\n",
        "\n",
        "- $f^2 \\approx 0.02$: **Small effect** (scientifically present, but possibly not worth spending millions of R&D dollars on).\n",
        "- $f^2 \\approx 0.15$: **Medium effect** (a solid, reliable driver of consumer behavior that demands corporate attention).\n",
        "- $f^2 \\approx 0.35$: **Large effect** (a very strong, practically dominant significant effect representing the absolute core foundation of the business to heavily leverage).\n",
        "\n",
        "**Industry Application:** In subscription software (SaaS), statistically significant factors like \"UI font choice\" might have an $f^2$ of $0.01$ (tiny), while \"Platform Uptime\" has an $f^2$ of $0.45$ (massive). Development engineering hours are thereby universally routed to maximizing uptime infrastructure instead of redesigning the fonts.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Python Example Code"
      ],
      "id": "9bf291ba"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import statsmodels.api as sm\n",
        "\n",
        "df = pd.read_csv('gogoro_data.csv')\n",
        "y = df['Sat1']\n",
        "X_full = sm.add_constant(df[['Brand1', 'Func1']])\n",
        "X_red = sm.add_constant(df[['Brand1']]) \n",
        "\n",
        "r2_full = sm.OLS(y, X_full).fit().rsquared\n",
        "r2_red = sm.OLS(y, X_red).fit().rsquared\n",
        "\n",
        "f2 = (r2_full - r2_red) / (1 - r2_full)\n",
        "print(\"Effect Size (f^2) for Function:\", round(f2, 3))"
      ],
      "id": "27f55e8c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
